crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: FILE-EXECUTABLE Portable Executable binary file magic detected
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET $FILE_DATA_PORTS -> $HOME_NET any ( msg:"FILE-EXECUTABLE Portable Executable binary file magic detected"; flow:to_client,established; file_data; content:"MZ"; byte_jump:4,58,relative,little; content:"PE|00 00|",within 4,distance -64; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop; service:ftp-data,http,imap,pop3; classtype:policy-violation; sid:15306; rev:22; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: FILE-EXECUTABLE McAfee LiveSafe malformed executable denial of service attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET $FILE_DATA_PORTS -> $HOME_NET any ( msg:"FILE-EXECUTABLE McAfee LiveSafe malformed executable denial of service attempt"; flow:to_client,established; file_data; content:"MZ",depth 2; content:"PE|00 00 4C 01|",within 6,distance 126; content:"|0B 01|",within 2,distance 18; content:".",within 400,distance 222; byte_test:4,>=,0x14000000,11,relative,little; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop; service:ftp-data,http,imap,pop3; reference:cve,2016-4535; classtype:attempted-dos; sid:39463; rev:4; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO EXE - Served Attached HTTP
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ET INFO EXE - Served Attached HTTP"; flow:to_client,established; http.header; content:"Content-Disposition"; nocase; content:"attachment"; nocase; file.data; content:"MZ"; within:2; classtype:misc-activity; sid:2014520; rev:8; metadata:created_at 2012_04_06, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2022_11_30;)

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Packed Executable Download"; flow:established,to_client; content:"|0d 0a 0d 0a|MZ"; isdataat:100,relative; content:"This program "; distance:0; content:"PE|00 00|"; distance:0; content:!"data"; within:400; content:!"text"; within:400; content:!"rsrc"; within:400; classtype:misc-activity; sid:2014819; rev:5; metadata:created_at 2012_05_30, performance_impact Moderate, confidence Medium, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2024_04_08;)

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Executable Download from dotted-quad Host
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Executable Download from dotted-quad Host"; flow:established,to_server; http.uri; content:".exe"; endswith; nocase; http.host; content:"."; offset:1; depth:3; content:"."; within:4; content:"."; within:4; pcre:"/^(?:\d{1,3}\.){3}\d{1,3}$/"; http.request_line; content:".exe HTTP/1."; fast_pattern; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2016141; rev:9; metadata:attack_target Client_and_Server, created_at 2013_01_03, deployment Perimeter, performance_impact Significant, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2024_04_09;)

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET HUNTING SUSPICIOUS Dotted Quad Host MZ Response

alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Observed UA-CPU Header"; flow:established,to_server; http.header_names; content:"|0d 0a|ua-cpu|0d 0a|"; nocase; threshold: type limit, track by_src, seconds 180, count 1; reference:url,oreilly.com/library/view/http-the-definitive/1565925092/re52.html; classtype:misc-activity; sid:2062715; rev:1; metadata:attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2025_06_03, deployment Perimeter, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2025_06_03;)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects requests to exclude files, folders or processes from Antivirus scanning using PowerShell cmdlets
Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.
